Dear Mom,

Thank you for making me who I am today. You gave birth to a fiery, creative, free-spirit and at times I know you didn’t know what to do with me 😉.

You are one of the hardest workers I know - you always had a full time job, yet somehow managed to still be my girl scout leader, throw the best birthday parties, and made sure our house was (mostly) in order.

I know I kept you on your toes with my outgoing personality against your soft, more reserved spirit, but I truly feel like you have always let me be me. You let me make my own choices which sometimes resulted in my own consequences, but you let me figure out life in the way that I needed to.

I don’t know if I ever truly knew how to appreciate you until I became a mama myself. Raising 3 different kiddos with 3 very different personalities, I know my one goal is that I raise them truly to be who THEY are created to be, who God has created to be.

So as I navigate my own kids; one with an independent, fiery spirit (like me), one who is reserved and soft spoken (like you), and one who just beats to his own drum - I know my one goal is to raise them how you raised me - to be kind, hardworking, and 100% uniquely themselves.

Love you Mom!

Happy Mothers Day ❤️

You're doing amazing, Mama. 🫶

Let's talk lumbar pillows and  a few ways to style them.

⭐️ Pair it with a cozy blanket! Some spaces only need one lumbar pillow due lack of space. Adding a blanket will help the pillow not look so out of place!

⭐️ Surround it with other throw pillows. Add a variety of shapes, colors, and sizes. Use a cute lumbar to give you some inspiration and a jumping off point for your other pillows.

⭐️ Bring in other lumbar pillows. Instead of adding a bunch of other throw pillows just add another lumbar. It makes the space seem full but also clean kept.

3 tips for using pillows in your bedroom 👇
Layer for Luxury: Create depth and comfort by layering different-sized pillows. Start with large pillows against the headboard, followed by standard or queen-sized pillows, and finish with decorative throw pillows in various shapes and textures.
Supportive Sleep: Choose pillows that suit your sleeping style. If you’re a side sleeper, opt for firmer pillows to support your neck and head. Back and stomach sleepers may prefer medium-firm pillows for proper spinal alignment.
Color and Style Coordination: Pillows can be a stylish bedroom accessory. Coordinate pillow colors and patterns with your bedding and overall bedroom decor to create a cohesive and visually pleasing look.
